				\begin{document}$$X= Cl, Br, I$$\end{document}. The chosen halide perovskites are taken in such a way that their respective cation and anion belong to the same group (A=alkali metal, B=crystallogen and C=halogen). This way of selecting the perovskites is advantageous as it not only facilitates the study of size effect but also hinders the charge effect as one moves down the periodic table.

